      <h2 class="section-heading lbrxt-tscale-d4">Typography</h2>

      <p>LibRext has a heavy focus on old-style serif fonts, as it looks to early Renaissance printed works as
        inspiration. The design system’s text styles are organized by "Font Roles" and "Document Roles”</p>

      <p>Font Roles are functional roles that can be shared by multiple elements.</p>

      <p>Document Roles correspond to common document styles and HTML/Markdown structure</p>

      <p>See <a href="./typography.html">Typography Specimens</a></p>

