      <h2 class="section-heading lbrxt-tscale-d4">Shapes</h2>

      <p>As for shapes, LibRext deals only with boxes. There are several options available for border radius, box shadow,
        widget heights, and card styles</p>

      <p>See <a href="./shapes.html">Shapes Specimens</a></p>

      <h3>Border Radius</h3>

      <p>A larger radius fits with larger boxes</p>

      <div class="page-example">
        <div class="shape-box-set border-radius">
          <% for(var i=0; i < borderRadiusSizes.length; i++) { %>
          <div class="shape-box-wrapper">
            <div class="shape-box lbrxt-bradius <%= borderRadiusSizes[i].sizeCode %>">
              <span class="box-text box-heading"><%= borderRadiusSizes[i].heading %></span><br />
              <span class="box-text box-body"><%= borderRadiusSizes[i].body %></span>
            </div>
          </div>
          <% } %>
        </div>
      </div>

      <h3>Box Shadow</h3>

      <p>Larger sizes imply more distance between box layer and parent layer</p>

